div.div:
How can you fall in love when you can’t even hold hands? Due to a childhood curse, anything that the Duke touches will die—which makes his flirty maid’s behavior all the more shocking! Is there a way for the Duke and his companions to somehow break the curse, or is he doomed to a life where love is forever out of his reach?
(Source: Funimation)

The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.
Kaiko sareta Ankoku Heishi (30-dai) no Slow na Second Life
Comedy, Ecchi, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

The dark soldier Dariel (30 years old) who can't use magic while in an army of demons, was fired for his lack of capacity. His desperate second life has begun in a human village where Dariel has arrived!

The story of Kim JaeHan starts now! A dad who only has eyes for his daughter faces a sudden death. His mission is now to protect his daughter DaHyun from the 12 bullies by using his powerful character from webtoon drawing when he was once alive! As a dad, he’ll never let his daughter get bullied. If he sees this?… he won’t let those bullies alone. Whoever touches my daughter, you’re fucked.

div.span: Turbulent Adventurers are Introverted, Observant, Feeling, Prospecting and Turbulent. They tend to have open minds, approaching life, new experiences, and people with grounded warmth.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely pragmatic and down-to-earth, with a strong focus on what is happening or very likely to happen.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely very good at improvising and adapting. Tends to be flexible and values novelty above stability.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
